   1:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c **** /**
   2:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   ******************************************************************************
   3:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   * @file    stm32f4xx_sdio.c
   4:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   * @author  MCD Application Team
   5:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   * @version V1.8.1
   6:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   * @date    27-January-2022
   7:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   * @brief   This file provides firmware functions to manage the following 
   8:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *          functionalities of the Secure digital input/output interface (SDIO) 
   9:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *          peripheral:
  10:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + Initialization and Configuration
  11:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + Command path state machine (CPSM) management
  12:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + Data path state machine (DPSM) management
  13:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + SDIO IO Cards mode management
  14:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + CE-ATA mode management
  15:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + DMA transfers management
  16:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *           + Interrupts and flags management
  17:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   *
  18:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c **** @verbatim
  19:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c **** 
  20:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  ===================================================================
  21:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****                  ##### How to use this driver #####
  22:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  ===================================================================
  23:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  [..]
  24:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) The SDIO clock (SDIOCLK = 48 MHz) is coming from a specific output of PLL 
  25:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (PLL48CLK). Before to start working with SDIO peripheral make sure that the
  26:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        PLL is well configured.
  27:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        The SDIO peripheral uses two clock signals:
  28:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) SDIO adapter clock (SDIOCLK = 48 MHz)
  29:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) APB2 bus clock (PCLK2)
  30:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccV61vMD.s 			page 2


  31:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        -@@- PCLK2 and SDIO_CK clock frequencies must respect the following condition:
  32:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            Frequency(PCLK2) >= (3 / 8 x Frequency(SDIO_CK))
  33:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  34:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Enable peripheral clock using RCC_APB2PeriphClockCmd(RCC_APB2Periph_SDIO, ENABLE).
  35:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  36:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) According to the SDIO mode, enable the GPIO clocks using 
  37:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        RCC_AHB1PeriphClockCmd() function. 
  38:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        The I/O can be one of the following configurations:
  39:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) 1-bit data length: SDIO_CMD, SDIO_CK and D0.
  40:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) 4-bit data length: SDIO_CMD, SDIO_CK and D[3:0].
  41:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) 8-bit data length: SDIO_CMD, SDIO_CK and D[7:0].      
  42:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  43:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Peripheral alternate function: 
  44:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Connect the pin to the desired peripherals' Alternate Function (AF) 
  45:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            using GPIO_PinAFConfig() function
  46:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Configure the desired pin in alternate function by: 
  47:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            GPIO_InitStruct->GPIO_Mode = GPIO_Mode_AF
  48:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Select the type, pull-up/pull-down and output speed via GPIO_PuPd, 
  49:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            GPIO_OType and GPIO_Speed members
  50:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Call GPIO_Init() function
  51:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  52:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Program the Clock Edge, Clock Bypass, Clock Power Save, Bus Wide, 
  53:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        hardware, flow control and the Clock Divider using the SDIO_Init()
  54:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        function.
  55:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  56:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Enable the Power ON State using the SDIO_SetPowerState(SDIO_PowerState_ON) 
  57:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        function.
  58:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****                 
  59:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Enable the clock using the SDIO_ClockCmd() function.
  60:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  61:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Enable the NVIC and the corresponding interrupt using the function 
  62:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        SDIO_ITConfig() if you need to use interrupt mode. 
  63:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  64:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) When using the DMA mode 
  65:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Configure the DMA using DMA_Init() function
  66:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Active the needed channel Request using SDIO_DMACmd() function
  67:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  68:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Enable the DMA using the DMA_Cmd() function, when using DMA mode. 
  69:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  70:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) To control the CPSM (Command Path State Machine) and send 
  71:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        commands to the card use the SDIO_SendCommand(), 
  72:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        SDIO_GetCommandResponse() and SDIO_GetResponse() functions. First, user has
  73:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        to fill the command structure (pointer to SDIO_CmdInitTypeDef) according 
  74:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        to the selected command to be sent.
  75:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        The parameters that should be filled are:
  76:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Command Argument
  77:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Command Index
  78:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Command Response type
  79:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Command Wait
  80:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) CPSM Status (Enable or Disable).
  81:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  82:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        -@@- To check if the command is well received, read the SDIO_CMDRESP
  83:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            register using the SDIO_GetCommandResponse().
  84:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            The SDIO responses registers (SDIO_RESP1 to SDIO_RESP2), use the
  85:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****            SDIO_GetResponse() function.
  86:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  87:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) To control the DPSM (Data Path State Machine) and send/receive 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccV61vMD.s 			page 3


  88:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        data to/from the card use the SDIO_DataConfig(), SDIO_GetDataCounter(), 
  89:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        SDIO_ReadData(), SDIO_WriteData() and SDIO_GetFIFOCount() functions.
  90:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
  91:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  *** Read Operations ***
  92:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  =======================
  93:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  [..]
  94:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) First, user has to fill the data structure (pointer to
  95:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        SDIO_DataInitTypeDef) according to the selected data type to be received.
  96:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        The parameters that should be filled are:
  97:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data TimeOut
  98:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Length
  99:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Block size
 100:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Transfer direction: should be from card (To SDIO)
 101:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Transfer mode
 102:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) DPSM Status (Enable or Disable)
 103:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****                                      
 104:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Configure the SDIO resources to receive the data from the card
 105:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        according to selected transfer mode (Refer to Step 8, 9 and 10).
 106:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
 107:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#)  Send the selected Read command (refer to step 11).
 108:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****                     
 109:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Use the SDIO flags/interrupts to check the transfer status.
 110:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
 111:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  *** Write Operations ***
 112:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  ========================
 113:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****  [..]
 114:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) First, user has to fill the data structure (pointer to
 115:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        SDIO_DataInitTypeDef) according to the selected data type to be received.
 116:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        The parameters that should be filled are:
 117:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data TimeOut
 118:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Length
 119:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Block size
 120:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Transfer direction:  should be to card (To CARD)
 121:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) Data Transfer mode
 122:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        (++) DPSM Status (Enable or Disable)
 123:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
 124:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Configure the SDIO resources to send the data to the card according to 
 125:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****        selected transfer mode (Refer to Step 8, 9 and 10).
 126:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****                      
 127:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Send the selected Write command (refer to step 11).
 128:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****                     
 129:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****    (#) Use the SDIO flags/interrupts to check the transfer status.
 130:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
 131:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c ****   
 132:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_sdio.c **** @endverbatim
